1
00:00:02,100 --> 00:00:04,060
"迷失" 前情提要...
Previously on "Lost"...

2
00:00:08,780 --> 00:00:11,700
- 这儿刻了一堆名字 Jacob在哪?  - 我不知道
- There are names. Where's Jacob?  - I don't know.

3
00:00:11,710 --> 00:00:14,370
- 为什么我的名字 会写在这上面?  - 他没告诉我
- Why is my name written down on this thing?  - He didn't tell me.

4
00:00:14,370 --> 00:00:16,150
- 他想从我这儿得到什么?  - 我得确保把你和Jack一起
- What does he want from me?  - I had to get you and Jack

5
00:00:16,150 --> 00:00:19,880
- 从神庙那儿叫过来  - 什么? 为什么?
- as far away from that temple as I possibly could.  - What? Why?

6
00:00:19,880 --> 00:00:21,380
因为有人马上就要去那儿了
'Cause someone's coming there.

7
00:00:22,880 --> 00:00:24,060
很坏的人
Someone bad.

8
00:00:29,650 --> 00:00:31,840
- 要走还来得及  - 我不走
- There's still time.  - Not for me.

9
00:01:02,680 --> 00:01:05,690
- 喔!  - 哦!
- Whoa!  - Oh!

10
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:08,350
Jarrah在哪?
Where's Jarrah?

11
00:01:08,950 --> 00:01:10,460
我没事 谢谢
I'm fine. Thank you.

12
00:01:10,460 --> 00:01:12,750
- 他在哪?!  - 他刚刚杀了Dogen
- Where is he?!  - Considering that he just killed Dogen,

13
00:01:12,750 --> 00:01:15,180
- 我想他不会乐意和我们凑成堆  - Dogen是谁?
- I don't think he's gonna be joining us.  - Who's Dogen?

14
00:01:15,180 --> 00:01:17,780
- 寺庙里主事的那个人  - Sayid把翻译官也杀了
- The guy in charge of the temple.  - Sayid killed the interpreter, too.

15
00:01:17,780 --> 00:01:20,140
- 你没搞错吧?  - 他站在他们的尸体旁
- Are you sure?  - He was standing over their dead bodies

16
00:01:20,140 --> 00:01:21,920
手里拿着把血淋淋的匕首 所以 嗯 我确定无疑
holding a bloody dagger, so, yeah, I'm pretty sure.

17
00:01:21,920 --> 00:01:23,560
你之前还说躲在寺庙里很安全
You said we were safe at the temple.

18
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:26,300
- 别人也是这么跟我说的  - 呃 海滩那边怎样了?
- That's what I was told.  - Well, what about the beach?

19
00:01:26,300 --> 00:01:28,770
- 什么海滩?  - 我们埋了Locke的那个海滩 他们住过的那个海滩
- What beach?  - Where we buried Locke, where they lived.

20
00:01:28,770 --> 00:01:30,080
至少在那儿 我们还能弄到水
At least we'll have the water at our backs,

21
00:01:30,080 --> 00:01:33,260
而且地形也熟悉 还有人有更好的建议么?
and it's familiar territory. Anybody else got a better idea?

22
00:01:34,150 --> 00:01:36,570
- 没 就去海滩吧  - 走那边
- No. The beach it is.  - That way.

23
00:01:36,570 --> 00:01:37,350
走吧
Move.

24
00:01:40,380 --> 00:01:43,170
... 就是在这座岛上 命运发生了转变
... and it was on this island that everything changed,

25
00:01:43,580 --> 00:01:47,270
最终尘埃落定...
that everything finally became clear...

26
00:01:47,270 --> 00:01:48,570
厄尔巴岛...
Elba...

27
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:52,580
正是拿破仑东山再起的发源地
is where Napoleon faced his greatest task.

28
00:01:52,580 --> 00:01:55,360
因为他最悲惨的下场 不是受到流放
Because exile wasn't the worst of his fate.

29
00:01:55,360 --> 00:01:58,930
真正让他无法忍受的 是权力的剥夺
What was truly devastating to him was the loss of his power.

30
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:02,760
当然 他们允许他保留皇帝的头衔
Sure, they allowed him to keep the title of Emperor.

31
00:02:03,260 --> 00:02:05,750
然而有名无实 毫无意义
But without any power, it was meaningless.

32
00:02:05,750 --> 00:02:07,680
他还不如死了更痛快
He might just as well have been dead.

33
00:02:09,240 --> 00:02:12,440
好吧 记得 明天五六节课我们继续 谢谢
All right, remember, five and six tomorrow. Thank you.

34
00:02:15,480 --> 00:02:17,280
Reynolds校长 上午好
Principal Reynolds. Good morning.

35
00:02:17,290 --> 00:02:18,760
跟我来
Walk with me.

36
00:02:21,430 --> 00:02:23,250
Linus 轮值表稍微调整了下
Linus, there's been a slight schedule shift.

37
00:02:23,250 --> 00:02:24,920
今天放学后
I'm going to need you to supervise detention

38
00:02:24,920 --> 00:02:26,420
- 你去监管那些留堂生  - 什么?
- after school today.  - What?

39
00:02:26,420 --> 00:02:27,500
确切说 这周每天都是你
In fact, all week.

40
00:02:27,500 --> 00:02:30,820
裁员 资金周转不灵 还有许多你不了解的麻烦事
Cutbacks, budget crises, events above your pay grade.

41
00:02:30,820 --> 00:02:33,570
毫无疑问 我们一个人得当两个用
Needless to say, some of us have to pull double duty.

42
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:35,000
但今天历史社团有活动啊
But we have history club today.

43
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:37,900
- 孩子们等着我呢...  - 历史社团只有5个学生 Linus
- Those kids need me...  - There are five students in history club, Linus.

44
00:02:37,901 --> 00:02:41,011
- 少了你 他们不会死的  - 我们不能找个 更胜任此事的人么?
- They'll live.  - Shouldn't we be encouraging the ones with ambition?

45
00:02:41,011 --> 00:02:43,031
得了吧 那个社团对他们来说无所谓 但对你不同
Spare me. The club isn't for them. It's for you.

46
00:02:43,041 --> 00:02:44,191
这让你有被需求感
It makes you feel needed.

47
00:02:44,191 --> 00:02:47,331
不幸的是 现在留堂生真的需要你
Unfortunately for now, you're needed in detention.

48
00:02:47,331 --> 00:02:49,181
多谢配合 Linus
Thanks for your understanding, Linus.

49
00:02:51,521 --> 00:02:54,181
其实 你该叫我Linus博士
It's Dr. Linus, actually.

50
00:02:56,821 --> 00:02:58,711
哦 我可爱的... 毁了!
Oh, for the love of... It's ruined!

51
00:02:58,711 --> 00:03:02,161
- 全毁了! 哦!  - 出... 什么事了 Leslie?
- It's ruined! Ohh!  - What's... what's the problem, Leslie?

52
00:03:02,231 --> 00:03:05,641
哦 福尔马林 沾到... 福尔马林了
Oh, formaldehyde. For... formaldehyde's the problem.

53
00:03:05,641 --> 00:03:08,431
你知道有什么能洗掉福尔马林么? 没有
You know what gets out formaldehyde? Nothin'.

54
00:03:08,431 --> 00:03:10,641
要是我有件实验室工作服
Maybe if I had some frickin' lab aprons,

55
00:03:10,641 --> 00:03:12,191
我就不用因为班上那些废物
I wouldn't have to pay for our incompetent students

56
00:03:12,191 --> 00:03:14,621
再跑去Marshalls 买过一件衣服了
with another trip to Marshalls.

57
00:03:14,622 --> 00:03:17,482
- 都是为了减少预算  - Reynolds难道就不能为了
- Budget cutbacks.  - How hard would it be for Reynolds

58
00:03:17,482 --> 00:03:19,272
科学知识的传播 稍微放点儿血么?
to spread around a little of the love to the sciences?

59
00:03:19,272 --> 00:03:21,922
我从上个世纪五十年代开始 就跟实验器材打交道
You know. I'm dealing with lab equipment in there from the 1950s.

60
00:03:21,922 --> 00:03:25,412
- 他干嘛搞成这样?  - Reynolds校长说了算
- Now why is that?  - Principal Reynolds is an administrator.

61
00:03:25,412 --> 00:03:27,472
他不是老师 他早忘了
He's not a teacher. He's forgotten what

62
00:03:27,472 --> 00:03:30,532
公立学校是啥体制的了
the public school system is about.

63
00:03:30,533 --> 00:03:33,133
嗯 作为啥狗屁养老金的交换条件 暑假不放假
Yeah, summers off in exchange for a crap pension.

64
00:03:33,133 --> 00:03:34,173
我得记得提醒他
I'm happy to remind him.

65
00:03:34,183 --> 00:03:37,543
不 照顾好孩子 这才是关键
No, taking care of the kids. That's what's important.

66
00:03:37,543 --> 00:03:39,033
好啦 你还一门心思在教学啊
Okay. You just keep dreamin'.

67
00:03:39,033 --> 00:03:42,643
哦 我知道你已经不搭理这一套了 但... 我不会放弃的
Oh, I know you've given up, but... I refuse to.

68
00:03:43,793 --> 00:03:45,773
或许你才配当校长
Maybe you should be the principal.

69
00:03:49,313 --> 00:03:51,853
别人也这么说
So says the substitute.

70
00:03:52,533 --> 00:03:54,083
我才配当校长 你为什么这么说呢?
What do you mean, I should be the principal?

71
00:03:54,083 --> 00:03:56,413
听上去 你很在乎这所学校
It just sounds like you care about this place.

72
00:03:56,423 --> 00:03:58,773
如果现任校长不在乎
And if the man in charge doesn't,

73
00:03:59,043 --> 00:04:01,163
那就到该换人的时候了
then maybe it's time for a change.

74
00:04:02,383 --> 00:04:04,973
我同意你的看法 但谁会听我的?
I appreciate the sentiment, but who's gonna listen to me?

75
00:04:08,023 --> 00:04:09,293
我就听着呢
I'm listenin'.

76
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,840
不如你告诉我 回那儿去的东西是什么?
How about you tell me what that thing back there was?

77
00:04:25,840 --> 00:04:29,620
- 那东西在雕像后杀了她的朋友  - 还杀了Jacob 对么?
- That thing's what killed her friends back at the statue.  - And Jacob, right?

78
00:04:30,980 --> 00:04:32,540
它也杀了Jacob
It killed Jacob, too.

79
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:34,420
嗯 当然 还杀了Jacob
Yeah, of course. And Jacob.

80
00:04:34,420 --> 00:04:35,260
当然
Of course.

81
00:04:36,900 --> 00:04:38,410
你叫Miles 对么?
You're Miles, right?

82
00:04:38,410 --> 00:04:39,650
全名Miles Straume?
Miles Straume?

83
00:04:39,650 --> 00:04:41,840
你可以和死者谈话
You communicate with the dead.

84
00:04:42,800 --> 00:04:43,740
准确地说 不行 我...
Not technically. I...

85
00:04:43,740 --> 00:04:46,050
我可以告诉你 人是怎么死的
I can tell you how someone died,

86
00:04:46,050 --> 00:04:47,910
分辨出他们死前的最后一丝想法
pick up their last thoughts before they check out,

87
00:04:47,910 --> 00:04:50,120
但我需要靠近他们的身边
but I need to be near their bodies.

88
00:04:50,630 --> 00:04:52,700
这是从Jacob身上掉下来的
This is what's left of Jacob's body.

89
00:04:56,307 --> 00:04:59,957
那么告诉我 Miles 他是怎么死的?
So tell me, Miles, how did he die?

90
00:05:34,837 --> 00:05:36,377
Linus杀了他
Linus killed him.

91
00:05:36,377 --> 00:05:37,727
什么?
What?

92
00:05:38,057 --> 00:05:39,627
他瞎说
That's not true.

93
00:05:41,877 --> 00:05:43,237
你确定?
Are you sure?

94
00:05:43,847 --> 00:05:46,037
呃 他站在Jacob尸体旁边
Well, he was standing over Jacob's dead body

95
00:05:46,037 --> 00:05:49,717
手上还拿着把血淋淋的匕首 所以... 嗯 我很确定
with a bloody dagger, so... yeah, I'm pretty sure.

96
00:05:59,317 --> 00:06:00,807
谢谢
Thank you.

97
00:06:03,007 --> 00:06:05,637
Jacob对我来说 就像爸爸一样
Jacob was the closest thing I ever had to a father.

98
00:06:10,407 --> 00:06:12,077
啊哦
Uh-oh.

99
00:06:24,557 --> 00:06:32,147

迷失 第6季第7集

100
00:07:06,777 --> 00:07:08,407
我要找些工具
I'm gonna look for some tools

101
00:07:08,437 --> 00:07:10,577
把住的地方收拾出来
and get to work on some shelter.

102
00:07:11,747 --> 00:07:14,907
剩下的人 看看还有什么能吃的 或者生个火
The rest of you, see what food's left, maybe get a fire going.

103
00:07:14,907 --> 00:07:16,847
对哦 生火可以搞定一切
Yeah, a fire'll fix everything.

104
00:07:22,187 --> 00:07:23,677
你要我做些什么吗?
Is there anything you'd like me to do?

105
00:07:34,237 --> 00:07:38,337
通灵这玩意儿... 太不靠谱了
You know, psychics... totally unreliable.

106
00:07:38,827 --> 00:07:42,787
Miles还想敲诈我...
Miles actually tried to blackmail me once into...

107
00:07:47,017 --> 00:07:48,737
你很会交朋友嘛 啊?
You make friends easy, don't ya?

108
00:08:04,327 --> 00:08:05,697
啊 啊
Ah. Ah.

109
00:08:05,697 --> 00:08:07,707
除此之外 他们还要再得
And on top of that, they'll have to convert

110
00:08:07,707 --> 00:08:09,927
两分才能扳平比分
on a 2-point conversion to make it a tie game.

111
00:08:10,577 --> 00:08:12,157
我给你做了顿火鸡大餐
I made you one of the turkey meals

112
00:08:12,157 --> 00:08:13,937
用了你喜欢的红莓果酱哦
with the cranberry sauce that you like.

113
00:08:14,387 --> 00:08:17,297
又是一顿营养均衡的大餐吧?
It ain't one of them "lean" deals, is it?

114
00:08:17,617 --> 00:08:19,917
是的 爸爸 这是有机食品
No. Dad. It's organic.

115
00:08:20,487 --> 00:08:21,967
我想让你保持身体健康
I'm trying to keep you healthy.

116
00:08:21,967 --> 00:08:23,817
貌似有点晚了吧
Well, it's a little too late for that.

117
00:08:24,867 --> 00:08:26,107
工作怎么样啊?
How was work?

118
00:08:27,097 --> 00:08:30,447
我有着近代欧洲史的博士学位...
I have a doctorate in modern European history...

119
00:08:32,877 --> 00:08:35,807
却被派去监管那些留堂生
And yet I'm babysitting burnouts in detention.

120
00:08:37,757 --> 00:08:38,947
留堂生 嗯?
Detention, huh?

121
00:08:40,117 --> 00:08:42,077
最糟的是
And the worst of it is,

122
00:08:42,077 --> 00:08:45,097
当我看着那些派给我监管的
as I look out at those ingrates

123
00:08:45,107 --> 00:08:47,427
混账学生时...
that I'm tasked with watching...

124
00:08:49,907 --> 00:08:52,067
我不由自主地想...
I can't help thinking...

125
00:08:57,147 --> 00:08:59,977
或许我还及不上他们中任何一个人
that maybe I'm more a loser than any of them.

126
00:09:05,077 --> 00:09:07,497
我真不希望看到你过着这样的日子 Ben
This isn't the life I wanted for you, Ben.

127
00:09:07,497 --> 00:09:08,907
我希望你能有更好的生活
I wanted so much more.

128
00:09:08,917 --> 00:09:10,037
我知道
I know.

129
00:09:10,887 --> 00:09:14,537
所以我才会去报名参加了那个该死的达摩组织
That's why I signed up for that damn Dharma Initiative

130
00:09:14,537 --> 00:09:16,507
还带了你去那个岛 还...
and took you to the island, and...

131
00:09:16,507 --> 00:09:18,357
他们都是些正直的人...
They were decent people...

132
00:09:19,077 --> 00:09:21,477
都比我聪明
Smarter than I'll ever be.

133
00:09:22,817 --> 00:09:25,277
想想如果我们留下来的话
Imagine how different our lives would've been

134
00:09:25,867 --> 00:09:27,347
生活会有多么不同
if we'd stayed.

135
00:09:27,767 --> 00:09:29,707
没错 我们会一直幸福地生活下去
Yes, we'd have both lived happily ever after.

136
00:09:29,707 --> 00:09:31,367
不 我是说真的 Ben
No, I'm serious, Ben.

137
00:09:33,237 --> 00:09:35,227
天晓得你会变成什么样
Who knows what you would've become.

138
00:09:39,907 --> 00:09:41,527
现在感觉好点了吗?
Now does that feel better?

139
00:09:41,527 --> 00:09:42,927
是的
Yes.

140
00:09:44,117 --> 00:09:45,237
谢谢
Thank you.

141
00:09:49,950 --> 00:09:50,900
是Alex?
Alex?

142
00:09:50,900 --> 00:09:51,990
Linus博士
Dr. Linus.

143
00:09:53,050 --> 00:09:55,720
今天您去哪儿了? 我们迫不得已 取消了历史社团的活动
Where were you today? We had to cancel history club.

144
00:09:56,150 --> 00:09:57,740
哦 对不起
Oh, I'm so sorry.

145
00:09:57,750 --> 00:09:59,330
我应该在门上贴张便条的
I should've put a note on the door.

146
00:09:59,640 --> 00:10:01,160
社团的活动要延期了
The club meetings have to be postponed.

147
00:10:01,160 --> 00:10:02,440
这个星期我都得去留堂生那儿
I'm in detention all week.

148
00:10:02,440 --> 00:10:05,020
哦 是吗? 您去做什么?
Oh, yeah? What'd you do?

149
00:10:06,130 --> 00:10:08,450
Reynolds校长让我去监管 所以...
Principal Reynolds needs me to cover, so...

150
00:10:08,980 --> 00:10:10,500
这周五有大学预修课程考试
A.P. Test this Friday.

151
00:10:10,960 --> 00:10:13,460
我还... 指望您能来辅导一下呢
I was... kinda counting on the tutoring.

152
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:18,830
那好 你看这样如何?
All right, how about this?

153
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:21,210
明早七点 图书馆见
Tomorrow morning, 7:00 a.m. In the library.

154
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,510
带咖啡来哦
And you bring the coffee.

155
00:10:24,630 --> 00:10:25,470
谢谢
Thanks.

156
00:10:26,390 --> 00:10:28,230
天啊 您真是个大好人 Linus博士
God, you're the best, Dr. Linus.

157
00:10:28,230 --> 00:10:30,080
- 别客气 Alex  - 好的
- My pleasure, Alex.  - Okay.

158
00:10:30,510 --> 00:10:31,870
再见
See you.

159
00:10:47,530 --> 00:10:51,020
打扰一下 我们要在这儿待多久啊?
Excuse me. How long are we going to stay here?

160
00:10:51,020 --> 00:10:53,010
我跟你说过 我还不知道
I told you. I don't know yet.

161
00:10:53,010 --> 00:10:54,830
我要去找我的丈夫
I need to find my husband.

162
00:10:55,760 --> 00:10:58,400
相信我 如果说有人想找到他的话 那肯定是我
Trust me, if anyone wants to find him, it's me.

163
00:10:58,420 --> 00:11:00,410
但我现在也全无头绪
But I don't know where to look.

164
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:03,410
你为什么想找到Jin啊?
Why do you want to find Jin?

165
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:06,330
因为你姓Kwon
Because your last name is Kwon.

166
00:11:06,670 --> 00:11:07,780
他也是
So is his.

167
00:11:08,330 --> 00:11:09,620
我不知道是不是
And I don't know whether

168
00:11:09,620 --> 00:11:12,050
